snippet: Michele Dunne, a former diplomat now with the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace, said Saturday that she was turned away at the Cairo airport.
abstract: Michele Dunne, American scholar and former diplomat who has been critical of government of Egyptian Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi, says she has been barred from entering Egypt.
lead_paragraph: Michele Dunne, a former diplomat now with the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace, said Saturday that she was turned away at the Cairo airport.

headline.main: Egypt Denies Entry to American Scholar Critical of Its Government
headline.print_headline: Egypt: American Scholar Is Turned Away at Airport
